properties.areaDesc: Maalaea Bay; Big Island Southeast Waters; Big Island Leeward Waters; Kaiwi Channel
properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued January 10 at 3:17AM HST until January 12 at 6:00PM HST by NWS Honolulu HI
properties.description:
* WHAT...East winds 20 to 30 kt with higher gusts and seas 8 to
13 feet.

* WHERE...Kaiwi Channel, Maalaea Bay, Big Island Leeward Waters
and Big Island Southeast Waters.

* WHEN...Until 6 PM HST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
A Small Craft Advisory means that wind speeds of 25 to 33 knots
and/or seas 10 feet or greater are expected to produce conditions
hazardous to small craft. Inexperienced mariners, especially
those operating smaller vessels, should avoid navigating in these
conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM HST SUNDAY... ...GALE WARNING IS CANCELLED
